author: COMSOL
description: This example uses the Battery with Binary Electrolyte interface for studying the charge and discharge of a nickelâ€“cadmium battery. The geometry is in one dimension, plus a cylindrically symmetric 1D geometry for proton diffusion in the positive electrode. The model is isothermal. Oxygen evolution/reduction at the positive electrode, mass transport of oxygen in the cell, and oxygen evolution/reduction at the negative electrode are additional processes also included in the model.
